cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.CE 

This paper presents a spiking neural network architecture that uses memristive devices as synaptic elements. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the physical properties of memristive devices, making cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) a likely category as well. The proposed mixed-signal analog-digital interfacing circuits fall under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also discusses the variability in conductance values and switching threshold of memristive devices, which could fall under cs.EM (Electronic Materials) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) categories, respectively.
